BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hkj13vJuP-6y5HtKhwvr5
SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260328T110956Z
DTSTART:20260330T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, March 30\, 2026\, 12 - 3:30pm\n\nTrained volunteers wi
	ll be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.\n\nL
	ocation Link:\n\nBroadview Branch\n\nRoom Location: Meeting Room\n\nDetail
	ed Description: This service is free and available to individuals only. Th
	e free service is not available for business tax returns. To receive tax h
	elp\, bring the following documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto identificatio
	n\, Social Security cards or Individual Taxpayer Identification Numbers \\
	(ITIN\\) for everyone listed on the tax return.\, Proof of income\, for ex
	ample\, W2s and 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Official documents 
	on Social Security Administration letterhead\, Medicare card \\(if Social 
	Security number is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to provide informat
	ion about health care coverage for each person on the return.\,\n\nRecomme
	nded:\n\nLast year&'s tax return\, if available\, Bank account and routing
	 numbers for direct deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer print-out
	s of any of these documents willbe accepted.\, Due to federal budget cuts 
	the IRS is unable to provide the Library with certain tax forms and instru
	ction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available online at\n\nwww.irs.gov .\
	, You may make free black-and-white prints of the forms from Library compu
	ters:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nAARP .\n\nEvent Log
	istics: AARP Tax Help locations serve anyone who earned less than $80\,000
	 in 2025.\, For eligibility details\, contact AARP at 888-227-7669.\n\nCon
	tact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206
	-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people
	 with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least se
	ven days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library program
	s are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/
	#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning
	 & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/20
	26-03-30T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:HviEiLDhJW3SN1Lk1Pbf-
SUMMARY:Virtual Workshop - Become a Small Business Owner Through Franchisin
	g
DTSTAMP:20260328T110956Z
DTSTART:20260330T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, March 30\, 2026\, 1 - 3pm\n\nIf you are considering fr
	anchising as a career option\, or actively working towards a franchise agr
	eement\, this program is for you.\n\nLocation Link: Online\n\nRegistration
	 Required: Registration is required.\n\nDetailed Description: This worksho
	p is designed both for individuals at the early stage of considering franc
	hising as a career option and those actively considering a franchise but w
	ho have not yet signed the agreement.\,\n\nTopics covered include:\n\nUnde
	rstand what is and is not a franchise\, Define a positive relationship wit
	h the franchisor\, Laws and legal requirements that apply to franchising i
	n Washington State\, Important criteria in choosing a franchise\, what que
	stions to ask and how to ask them\, Research hints and tools\, A view into
	 a method to segment franchises in six different categories\, A discussion
	 on financing\, incorporation and preparation relating to a franchise awar
	d\, Navigating the myriad of franchise opportunities available\, Doing you
	r due diligence\, Narrowing down your search\, What to consider and what m
	atters to you\, Answers to your specific questions\, About the Presenter:\
	,\n\nJeff Levy\n\nis an educator\, author and coach. Herelocated from NYC 
	for a 3-person tech startup up in WA State\, has managed up to 300 people 
	across international borders and has been a franchisee since 2002. His per
	sonal experiences include raising capital\, starting and acquiring busines
	ses and investing in a franchise during a career transition. He has also s
	erved on multiple boards\, committees and has contributed voluntary work o
	n community projects.\, Registration is required. Register\n\nhere .\n\nCo
	ntact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 20
	6-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for peopl
	e with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least s
	even days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library progra
	ms are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events
	/#/details/virtual-workshop-become-a-small-business-owner-through-franchis
	ing/18407672/2026-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/virtual-workshop-become-a
	-small-business-owner-through-franchising/18407672/2026-03-30T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
