BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:AidTFSpUGQYUAvAj8bsCV
SUMMARY:Learn at LANGSTON: Healing Drum Workshop
DTSTAMP:20260328T110956Z
DTSTART:20260331T004500Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Community\,Ethnic/Cultural\,Music\,Training-Cla ss
	es/Workshops\n\nNeighborhoods: Central Area/Squire Park\n\nSponsoring Orga
	nization: LANGSTON\n\nContact: Jahi McGhee\n\nContact Phone: 2066844758\n\
	nContact Email: langston.institute@seattle.gov\n\nAudience: All\n\nPre-Reg
	ister: Yes\n\nCost: Free\n\nLink: https://www.langstonseattle.org/programs
	/healing-drum-workshop/\n\nDrums are provided. All ages. No experience nec
	essary.\n\nThe Hawk Foundation for Research and Education in African Cultu
	re brings master drummers t o LANGSTON to engage in a well-researched peda
	gogy of community healing through African drumming.\n\nThe Hawk Foundation
	 is a Washington-based drum and education organization that utilizes West 
	African and African American music to promote education\, team bonding\, o
	rganizational de velopment\, and research-based therapy. Through history\,
	 Yoruba stories and classic drum rhythms\, this class has reconnected stud
	ents to the drum\, the past\, and themselves.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/learn-at-langston-healing-drum-workshop/18448016/2026
	-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/learn-at-langston-healing
	-drum-workshop/18448016/2026-03-30T00
LOCATION:Langston Hughes Performing Arts Institute\, 104 17th Avenue South 
	West Room\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT45M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:OtmDu9PycRODggwNC3h5j
SUMMARY:Learn at LANGSTON: Karate with Tyron
DTSTAMP:20260328T110956Z
DTSTART:20260331T004500Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Community\,Hobbies\,Sports/Recreation\,Training -C
	lasses/Workshops\n\nNeighborhoods: Central Area/Squire Park\n\nSponsoring 
	Organization: LANGSTON\n\nContact: Jahi McGhee\n\nContact Phone: 206684475
	8\n\nContact Email: langston.institute@seattle.gov\n\nAudience: All\n\nPre
	-Register: Yes\n\nCost: Free\n\nLink: https://www.langstonseattle.org/prog
	rams/karate-with-tyron/\n\nTyron Asphy\, founder of Japan-American Butokuk
	an Karate Association\, has returned to the Langston Hughes Performing Art
	s Institute\, where he taught community karate classes over 40 years ago.\
	n\nTyron works with five instructors to offer martial arts classes to stud
	ents ages 5 to 75 years old. His commitment to bringing access to discipli
	ne\, flexibility\, and self-defense to the Black youth and other residents
	 in the Central District area is invaluable to the overall health and well
	-being of our community.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/
	learn-at-langston-karate-with-tyron/18448015/2026-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoda
	y - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/learn-at-langston-karate-
	with-tyron/18448015/2026-03-30T00
LOCATION:Langston Hughes Performing Arts Institute\, 104 17th Avenue South 
	West Room\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H45M
END:VEVENT
